COMMENTS="OpenLDAP server can be started or stopped with the following command:
			sudo /usr/local/etc/init.d/openldap-server start|stop

		Init script starts the server with the default configuration from the file /usr/local/etc/default/openldap-server

		Add these to your backup list (/opt/.filetool.lst) if you want changes to be persistent
			usr/local/etc/default/openldap-server
			usr/local/etc/openldap/slapd.conf

		This extension is PPI compatible."
